msgctxt "524"
msgid "A single malt whisky aged in sherry barrels for a balanced flavor."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "540"
msgid "This limited edition Yamazaki was created in 1999 to commemorate Suntory's 100 year anniversary. A long aging process in sherry wood barrels produces a perfect balance."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "544"
msgid "I'm certain anyone fortunate enough to enjoy this rare whisky will experience pure bliss. Its price puts it just within reach, as far as dream whiskies go. "
msgstr ""

msgctxt "548"
msgid "I enjoy drinking it on special occasions."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "596"
msgid "Around 80 percent of this whisky is matured in sherry casks, while the other 20 percent spent its time in American and Mizunara oak casks."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "612"
msgid "This eighteen-year-old Japanese whisky has earned the loyalty of an ever-increasing international following of Japanese whisky fans abroad."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "616"
msgid "Among all of Yamazaki's highly decorated repertoire, this whisky has received the most awards."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "620"
msgid "Profound, aged flavor, dry fruitiness imparted by the cherry wood cask..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "624"
msgid "And a fragrant hint of chocolate on your palate will leave you stunned by this full-bodied whisky."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "628"
msgid "You've got to try this world-renowned flavor for yourself."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "668"
msgid "A Yamazaki whisky made with carefully selected, mature malts for a flavorful, smooth finish."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "684"
msgid "This is one of Japan's top single malt whiskies. It's become such a status symbol that whisky aficionados the world over have heard of it. "
msgstr ""

msgctxt "688"
msgid "They use carefully selected, perfectly matured single malts to get that great, smooth flavor. It's popular overseas, too."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "740"
msgid "A whisky made in the Southern Alps of Japan. Has a fruity flavor with smoky accents."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "756"
msgid "This one's made at Suntory's Hakushu distillery in Japan's South Alps, an area famous for its mountain spring water."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "760"
msgid "Its fruity, creamy flavor combined with a distinctly smoky accent makes for a superb drinking experience. "
msgstr ""

msgctxt "764"
msgid "I recommend taking the first drink straight up, to fully appreciate its quality."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "812"
msgid "The champion of single malt whiskies."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "828"
msgid "The Macallan premium single malt is the champion of single malt whiskies. This 52 year old whisky made in 1946 wasn't put on the market until the new millennium in 1999. "
msgstr ""

msgctxt "832"
msgid "The sherry and wood flavors that are characteristic of The Macallan are more subdued, giving it more of an Islay malt peatiness."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "836"
msgid "They say this was the result of a coal shortage right after World War II, when significant amounts of peat were used in the malting process."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "840"
msgid "Expensive and extremely rare, but you can almost taste the history behind it."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "884"
msgid "A cheaper, yet still tasty, alternative to some of the pricier Macallan whiskies."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "900"
msgid "The standard of The Macallan line, aged entirely in sherry barrels. It's perfect for people who want to enjoy The Macallan without breaking the bank. "
msgstr ""

msgctxt "904"
msgid "It may be the standard bearer of the line, but it's guaranteed to deliver \"The Macallan\" taste! I recommend you experience its sweet, full flavor and aroma for yourself.  "
msgstr ""

msgctxt "956"
msgid "Characterized by an intensely smoky flavor and a smooth, dry body."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "972"
msgid "It's safe to say this 10 year Laphroaig is the standard-bearer of the brand. It's characterized by an intensely smoky flavor and a smooth, dry body."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "976"
msgid "And it has more than its share of quirks, so most people either love it or hate it. If you end up loving this one, it'll be one drink you'll never forget. "
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1028"
msgid "A 12-year-old Scotch whisky with ripe, floral overtones."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1044"
msgid "That's the standard of the Bowmore line. Sherry barrels give it its uniquely ripe, floral overtones. Seaweeds unique to Islay give it a distinctive flavor and saltiness."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1048"
msgid "These qualities have earned it the title \"Queen of Islay.\" It stands a cut above the rest of the single malt 12-year-old whiskies.   "
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1100"
msgid "The best-selling single malt whisky in the world, known for its light and fresh flavor."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1116"
msgid "Glenfiddich 12 Years is the best selling single malt whisky in the world. This bottle set the industry standard for a single malt. You'll find it light and fresh."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1120"
msgid "The nose is full of fruit, and it has a clean finish, making it exceptionally easy to drink. "
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1124"
msgid "Its light flavor makes it popular with the ladies and anyone new to single malt whiskies.  "
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1172"
msgid "An extraordinary malt Scotch whisky with a tropical body and oaky notes. Aged in bourbon casks since 1964."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1188"
msgid "It has a slightly smoky flavor coupled with a ripe, fruity aroma. Its crisp aftertaste is also quite unique. "
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1192"
msgid "Since it was bottled without being overly chilled, you can still enjoy the flavors imparted by the aging process. I think it's considered a collector's item."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1244"
msgid "One of Japan's premium brands, known internationally for its mellow flavor."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1260"
msgid "This is a premium Japanese whisky that has won over whisky lovers around the world. "
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1264"
msgid "This whisky starts with a single malt aged in Japanese Mizunara oak and then blended with over thirty different, painstakingly selected single malts. "
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1268"
msgid "The mellow flavor produced by this process has earned it a gold prize in international competition.  "
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1272"
msgid "The finish is particularly good."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1276"
msgid "This bottle is popularly given in gift exchanges. Not that I've ever been gifted one..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1316"
msgid "The father of Japanese whisky, and possibly the most popular whisky in all of Japan."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1332"
msgid "Kakubin is probably the most popular whisky in Japan, wouldn't you agree? Some call it the father of Japanese whisky."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1336"
msgid "Its popularity shows no signs of waning,  even after seventy years on the market. It has a sweet aroma, depth, and full body. "
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1340"
msgid "The name Kakubin comes from its unique squared bottle shape.  "
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1388"
msgid "A carefully distilled spirit with a bright aroma and sweet fullness."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1404"
msgid "Another extremely popular Japanese whisky. Malt whisky aged in sherry barrels at the Yamazaki Distillery are blended with carefully selected malt and grain whiskies."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1408"
msgid "It has a bright aroma and delivers a sweet fullness in the mouth, and the finish is deep and mellow. "
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1412"
msgid "A lot of people call it Daruma, because the round shape of its bottle looks like a Daruma doll."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1460"
msgid "The crown jewel of the Ballantine's brand, crafted from a combination of over forty single malts."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1476"
msgid "This is the ultimate blended whisky. It boasts a rich and smooth taste only made possible by combining over forty single malts. "
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1480"
msgid "This could very well be called the crown jewel of Ballantine's whisky blending skills. It's well loved the world over, to the point of some calling it <Italic>the</Italic> scotch. "
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1532"
msgid "Standard Ballantine's scotch. Not too heavy, not too light, but just right."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1548"
msgid "That's a standard Scotch, made from a blend of over forty varieties of single malts. Not too heavy, not too light. It's got a great balance to it.   "
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1552"
msgid "And the price isn't too high, either. I recommend it to casual Scotch drinkers. It's also a nice intro to blended whiskies, if you've never tried them before."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1604"
msgid "A remarkable specimen made by pairing the finest grapes with Borderies spirits."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1620"
msgid "A remarkable specimen from France. This one won a top prize in an international cognac competition. "
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1624"
msgid "A blend of grapes from the four finest crus in the Cognac region produces a full but smooth palate. You haven't tasted cognac until you've tried this one.   "
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1676"
msgid "One of the world's favorite beers, enjoyed by people in 140 countries around the globe."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1692"
msgid "Carlsberg is known for brewing lagers, but they licensed Suntory to create this draft beer using their own in-house technique."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1696"
msgid "Together, they've created Carlsberg's first draft beer, found only here in Japan."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1700"
msgid "It has an impressively clean taste that goes well with all sorts of food."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1748"
msgid "A clean spring water soju made with premier Korean barley."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1764"
msgid "A prime example of Korean soju. A natural spring water base gives it a clean taste, while premium Korean barley gives it a mellow, rounded flavor. "
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1768"
msgid "It's not all that expensive, either. I'd say it offers excellent value for the price. I used to drink this all the time, and its taste is still as familiar as an old friend."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1772"
msgid "To me, this bottle of soju brings back a lot of fond memories.  "
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1820"
msgid "A standard rum with an oaky flavor and notes of vanilla."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1836"
msgid "A rum sold by Suntory. Rum is produced from sugarcane which is wrung and refined into molasses."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1840"
msgid "The color, grade, and flavor of rum varies with the production process, and Suntory Rum Gold is an amber-colored medium-bodied rum."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1844"
msgid "It's frequently used as a cocktail base, and it's reasonably priced so it won't break the bank, but..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1848"
msgid "Rum-based cocktails tend to be sweet and go down easy, so drink responsibly."
msgstr ""

